Description: (Objective of what you are trying to test.)

When a system performs trusted boot, BIOS performs measurements at various stages and stores them in PCR 0-7 (Platform config registers) in TPM. The PCR 0-7 values need to be consistent on each system from boot to boot. The values also need to be consistent on identically configured systems. If there is any change in the measurement, then it may indicate a malware attack. This is the premise in which trusted boot operates. 
Preconditions: (What conditions must be met or data must exist in the system for this test to be executed?)
TPM module is connected to board. PCR reading tool is ready.
USB flash disk with PCR reading tool is connected to SUT firstly.
PCR value can be read via EFI Tool or Tboot OS TPM file(such as ‘cat /sys/class/misc/tpm0/device/pcrs’)
